    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReferenceConcurrentNavigableMap

    class ReferenceConcurrentMap<K,V>
extends ReferenceMap<K,V>
implements java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V>
    A referenced hash map, that encapsulates and utilises any ConcurrentMap implementation passed in at construction. Based on any ConcurrentMap implementation, it doesn't accept null keys or values. It is recommended although not mandatory to use identity based References for keys, unexpected results occur when relying on equal keys, if one key is no longer strongly reachable and has been garbage collected and removed from the Map. If either a key or value, is no longer strongly reachable, their mapping will be queued for removal and garbage collection, in compliance with the Reference implementation selected.
    Since:
    2.3
    Author:
    Peter Firmstone.
